.TH "FILES" "1" "2026\-04\-11" "Winix" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
files \- find files by name, size, date, type, and content
.SH SYNOPSIS
\f[B]files\f[R] [\f[I]options\f[R]] [\f[I]paths\f[R]\&...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Walks one or more directories (default: \f[B].\f[R] ) and prints
matching file paths to stdout, one per line.
Supports glob and regex name matching, type filtering, size and date
ranges, text/binary detection, and structured output.
.PP
Results are printed to stdout; the \f[B]\(enjson\f[R] summary goes to
stderr so it does not pollute piped output.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\f[B]\-g\f[R], \f[B]\(englob\f[R] \f[I]PATTERN\f[R]
Match filenames against a glob pattern (repeatable).
.TP
\f[B]\-e\f[R], \f[B]\(enregex\f[R] \f[I]PATTERN\f[R]
Match filenames against a regex (repeatable).
.TP
\f[B]\(enext\f[R] \f[I]EXT\f[R]
Match file extension, e.g.\ \f[B]cs\f[R], \f[B]log\f[R] (repeatable).
.TP
\f[B]\-t\f[R], \f[B]\(entype\f[R] \f[I]TYPE\f[R]
Filter by type: \f[B]f\f[R] (file), \f[B]d\f[R] (directory), \f[B]l\f[R]
(symlink).
.TP
\f[B]\(entext\f[R]
Only text files.
.TP
\f[B]\(enbinary\f[R]
Only binary files.
.TP
\f[B]\(enmin\-size\f[R] \f[I]SIZE\f[R]
Minimum file size (e.g.\ \f[B]100k\f[R], \f[B]10M\f[R], \f[B]1G\f[R]).
.TP
\f[B]\(enmax\-size\f[R] \f[I]SIZE\f[R]
Maximum file size (e.g.\ \f[B]100k\f[R], \f[B]10M\f[R]).
.TP
\f[B]\(ennewer\f[R] \f[I]DURATION\f[R]
Modified within \f[I]DURATION\f[R] (e.g.\ \f[B]1h\f[R], \f[B]30m\f[R],
\f[B]7d\f[R]).
.TP
\f[B]\(enolder\f[R] \f[I]DURATION\f[R]
Not modified within \f[I]DURATION\f[R] (e.g.\ \f[B]1h\f[R],
\f[B]7d\f[R]).
.TP
\f[B]\-d\f[R], \f[B]\(enmax\-depth\f[R] \f[I]N\f[R]
Maximum directory depth (0 = search root only).
.TP
\f[B]\-L\f[R], \f[B]\(enfollow\f[R]
Follow symbolic links.
.TP
\f[B]\(enabsolute\f[R]
Output absolute paths.
.TP
\f[B]\(enno\-hidden\f[R]
Skip hidden files and directories.
.TP
\f[B]\(engitignore\f[R]
Respect \f[B].gitignore\f[R] rules.
.TP
\f[B]\-i\f[R], \f[B]\(enignore\-case\f[R]
Case\-insensitive name matching.
.TP
\f[B]\(encase\-sensitive\f[R]
Case\-sensitive name matching.
.TP
\f[B]\-l\f[R], \f[B]\(enlong\f[R]
Tab\-delimited detail output (path, size, date, type).
.TP
\f[B]\-0\f[R], \f[B]\(enprint0\f[R]
Null\-delimited output (for \f[B]xargs \-0\f[R]).
.TP
\f[B]\(enndjson\f[R]
Streaming NDJSON to stdout, one JSON object per file.
.TP
\f[B]\(enjson\f[R]
JSON summary to stderr on exit.
.TP
\f[B]\(endescribe\f[R]
Print machine\-readable metadata and exit.
.TP
\f[B]\(encolor\f[R]
Force coloured output.
.TP
\f[B]\(enno\-color\f[R]
Disable coloured output.
.TP
\f[B]\(enversion\f[R]
Show version.
.TP
\f[B]\-h\f[R], \f[B]\(enhelp\f[R]
Show help.
.SH SIZE UNITS
\f[B]\(enmin\-size\f[R] and \f[B]\(enmax\-size\f[R] accept an optional
unit suffix: \f[B]k\f[R] (1024 bytes), \f[B]M\f[R] (megabytes),
\f[B]G\f[R] (gigabytes).
No suffix means bytes.
Examples: \f[B]500\f[R], \f[B]10k\f[R], \f[B]2M\f[R], \f[B]1G\f[R].
.SH DURATION UNITS
\f[B]\(ennewer\f[R] and \f[B]\(enolder\f[R] accept a number followed by
a unit: \f[B]s\f[R] (seconds), \f[B]m\f[R] (minutes), \f[B]h\f[R]
(hours), \f[B]d\f[R] (days), \f[B]w\f[R] (weeks).
Examples: \f[B]30m\f[R], \f[B]1h\f[R], \f[B]7d\f[R].
.SH EXIT CODES
.TP
\f[B]0\f[R]
Success.
.TP
\f[B]1\f[R]
Runtime error (permission denied, invalid path).
.TP
\f[B]125\f[R]
Usage error (bad arguments).
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
\f[B]NO_COLOR\f[R]
If set, disables coloured output (no\-color.org).
.SH EXAMPLES
.IP
.EX
files src \-\-ext cs

files . \-\-text \-\-type f

files . \-\-newer 1h \-\-type f

files . \-\-long \-\-ext cs

files . \-\-gitignore \-\-no\-hidden \-\-ext cs

files . \-\-glob \(aq*.log\(aq | wargs rm

files . \-\-ndjson | jq \(aq.name\(aq

files . \-\-min\-size 1k \-\-max\-size 10M

files . \-\-glob \(aq*.log\(aq \-\-print0 | xargs \-0 rm
.EE
